# yuanrong-datasystem vs vibe-coding-files

## Upstream (canonical)

- **Repository name**: `yuanrong-datasystem`
- **Upstream URL**: https://gitcode.com/openeuler/yuanrong-datasystem

Use this URL when referring to the official open-source project. Local clone path is commonly a sibling of `vibe-coding-files`, e.g. `../yuanrong-datasystem/` (override with `DATASYSTEM_ROOT` / `YUANRONG_DATASYSTEM_ROOT`).

## What goes where

| Location | Contents |
|----------|----------|
| **`yuanrong-datasystem`** | Product **source code**, official build chain, and **repository structure** documented under **`.repo_context/`** (see that repo’s `.cursor/rules/repo-context.mdc`). |
| **`vibe-coding-files`** | **Everything else**: verification/analysis scripts, `plans/`, narrative `docs/`, run artifacts under `results/` or `plans/.../runs/`, outputs under `workspace/` when used, Cursor skills, and any intermediate outputs tied to development workflow — **not** a substitute for `.repo_context/` in the code repo. Scripted writes follow **`.cursor/rules/workspace-output-hygiene.mdc`** (stable defaults; no per-run file sprawl unless opted in). |

## Naming note (product vs repo)

The Git repository directory is **`yuanrong-datasystem`**. Published Python packages, Helm chart names, or docs paths may still use **`openyuanrong`** / **`openyuanrong_datasystem`**; do not rename the clone directory to match those — keep **`yuanrong-datasystem`** for paths and scripts unless the user standardizes otherwise.
